Lance Corporal Leonard Keysor served during World War I in Gallipoli . 
  He was awarded a Victoria Cross for his 48-hour effort to throw live grenades back at the enemy . 
  The Victoria Cross is the highest military honour an Australian can receive . 
  LCpl Keysor was awarded the VC for his bravery in the trenches of Lone Pine . 
  He picked up Turkish bombs and threw them back to save his comrades . 
  He even caught some of the bombs in mid-air . 
 